    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>CANADIAN FORESTRY STRIKE</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Timothy Pritchard</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Pritchard, Timothy</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>More than third of 32,000 forest workers in British Columbia represented by Industrial Wood and Allied Workers of Canada union have gone on strike, and province is threatened with complete shutdown of industry; employer bargaining group is Forest Industrial Relations (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>More than a third of the 32,000 forest workers in British Columbia have gone on strike, and the province is threatened with a complete shutdown of the industry, one of the most important in western Canada. On Tuesday, 12,000 members of the Industrial Wood and Allied Workers of Canada union went on strike after a breakdown of talks with an employer bargaining group, Forest Industrial Relations. While the union is seeking higher wages and pensions, the employers group is seeking concessions that would help companies raise their profit.</p>
        <p>Timothy Pritchard</p>
      </block>
